@Jodonny  What I do as an exercise to get my head in the game when I know I'm not hearing things right, is to either have a really hot or really cold shower - I can't say for sure why this works for me, but if I was to rationalise it, I'd say it's because it shocks my mind into a heightened state of awareness, probably due to the shock of the extreme temperature change. I stick it out for around 10 minutes, and when I go back I'm almost always hearing things the way I should be.

And if I've the time, for an extra boost of awareness, when I come back from my shower I spend about 10-20 minutes just listening to music of a similar genre to what I'm working on, without changing the volume level between songs or when I go back to my DAW. When I stick to this routine I usually do my best work.

I've also *really* fucked up some mixes due to attempting to get them done when I ain't hearing things right. I also have sinus issues, but maybe my senses aren't warmed up. I dunno. The human body is crazy
